label.value: loop-mediated isothermal amplification

definition.value: An enzymatic amplification in which a piece of DNA is amplified at a constant temperature of 60 - 65 degree C using either two or three sets of primers and a polymerase with high strand displacement activity in addition to a replication activity. This amplification does not need thermal cyclers and may be a low cost alternative to PCR.

label.value: detection of pathogenic organisms objective

definition.value: An organism feature identification objective that aims to detect whether an organism contains pathogenic organisms.

label.value: insecticide resistance detection objective

definition.value: An organism feature identification objective that aims to detect insecticide resistance of an insect.

label.value: arthropod meal of blood specimen

definition.value: A specimen of the blood ingested by an arthropod.

label.value: polymerase chain reaction assay

definition.value: An assay that uses polymerase chain reaction technique to amplify DNA.

label.value: restriction fragment length polymorphism assay

definition.value: An assay that uses digestion of DNA with specific restriction enzymes followed by gel electropheresis to detect differences in the sizes of the generated fragments that are due to genetic differences (polymorphisms) in homologous sequences.

label.value: DNA fingerprinting assay

definition.value: An assay to identify a specific individual organism from a DNA specimen by looking at unique patterns in their DNA.

label.value: insecticide resistance assay

definition.value: An assay that aims to detect the presence and/or frequency of resistance to insecticides in an organism or organism population.

label.value: insecticide resistance by monitoring known mutations assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that detects, in a population, presence and frequency of mutant alleles for previously characterized mutations with insecticide resistance phenotypes.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is based on determination the catalytic activity of an enzyme associated with insecticide resistance phenotypes.

label.value: insecticide resistance bioassay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is typically conducted to measure the effects of a substance on a living organism.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting alpha esterase activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures activity of alpha esterase.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting beta esterase activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures activity of beta esterase.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting acetylcholinesterase activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures activity of acetylcholinesterase.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting glutathione S-transferase activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures activity of glutathione S-transferase (GST).

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting carboxylic ester hydrolase activity assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures activity of carboxylic ester hydrolase using p-nitrophenyl acetate as a substrate.

label.value: insecticide resistance by detecting mixed-function oxidase assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by detecting enzyme activity assay that measures whether mixed-function oxidase activity present.

label.value: direct insecticide resistance bioassay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance bioassay without the use of any synergist.

label.value: topical application insecticide resistance bioassay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance bioassay by adding insecticide directly to the thorax of the insect.

label.value: direct insecticide resistance diagnostic assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance assay that at preset insecticide dosage scoring mortality to determine resistance of a population.

label.value: insecticide resistance dose response assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance assay in which an insect population is exposed to a range of insecticide dosage scoring mortality to determine resistance.

label.value: insecticide resistance time response assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance assay to determine resistance as a consequence of the time of exposure to insecticide.

label.value: Centre for Disease Control and Prevention bottle bioassay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance diagnostic assay performs in a glass bottle coated with insecticides for detecting resistance to insecticides in vector populations.

label.value: WHO cone kit diagnostic assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance diagnostic assay uses WHO cone kit.

label.value: WHO paper kit diagnostic assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance diagnostic assay uses WHO paper kit.

label.value: WHO larvicide diagnostic assay

definition.value: A direct insecticide resistance diagnostic assay tests survival of larvae in a medium supplemented with insecticide.

label.value: insecticide resistance dose response by bottle assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance dose response assay that performs in a glass bottle coated with insecticides.

label.value: insecticide resistance dose response by survival of larvae assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance dose response assay that tests survival of larvae in a medium supplemented with insecticide.

label.value: insecticide resistance dose response by WHO paper kit assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance dose response assay using WHO paper kit.

label.value: insecticide resistance time response by bottle assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance time response assay that is performed in a glass bottle coated with insecticides, with the presence of a synergist.

label.value: insecticide resistance time response by WHO paper kit assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance time response assay using WHO paper kit, with the presence of a synergist.

label.value: insecticide resistance by amplification refractory mutation system assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by monitoring known mutations assay that detects any mutation involving single base changes or small deletions using amplification refractory mutation system (ARMS). The ARMS is based on the use of sequence-specific PCR primers that allow amplification of test DNA only when the target allele is contained within the sample. Following an ARMS reaction the presence or absence of a PCR product is diagnostic for the presence or absence of the target allele. It can be used to analyze human genomic DNA for one or more mutations.

label.value: insecticide resistance by primer introduced restriction analysis PCR assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by monitoring known mutations assay that detects Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs) using PCR technique and mismatched primers that is close to the mutation of interest and digested the PCR productions using restriction enzymes.

label.value: insecticide resistance by nested polymerase chain reaction assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by monitoring known mutations assay that detects gene mutation based on nested polymerase chain reaction technique.

label.value: insecticide resistance by ligase detection reaction assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is based on monitoring known mutations using ligase detection reaction exquisitely discriminate between a mismatched and complementary DNA helix.

label.value: insecticide resistance by ligase detection reaction-fluorescent microsphere assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by ligase detection reaction assay that uses fluorescently labeled conserved probes in ligase detection reaction.

label.value: insecticide resistance by PCR amplification of specific alleles assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is based on monitoring known mutations by PCR amplification of specific alleles to detect polymorphic or mutant alleles.

label.value: insecticide resistance by fluorogenic PCR assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is based on monitoring known mutations by PCR technique that uses target specific probes labeled with fluorogenic chromophores to detect gene mutation.

label.value: insecticide resistance by PCR-RFLP assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance by monitoring known mutations assay based on restriction fragment length polymorphism assay.

label.value: insecticide resistance by short interspersed elements PCR assay

definition.value: An insecticide resistance assay that is based on monitoring known mutations by PCR amplification of short interspersed elements (SINEs).

label.value: pathogen detection assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that detects pathogens.

label.value: VectorTest assay

definition.value: A pathogen detection assay that identifies the presence or absence of specific peptide epitopes of circumsporozoite (CS) protein of the most important Plasmodium falciparum and two strains (variants 210 and 247) of the more widespread Plasmodium vivax using a dipstick wicking test strip.

label.value: pathogen detection by Rapid Analyte Measurement Platform assay

definition.value: A pathogen detection assay that is based on Rapid Analyte Measurement Platform (RAMP) technology to quantify immunologically active substances.

label.value: pathogen detection by loop-mediated isothermal amplification assay

definition.value: A pathogen detection assay that is based on loop-mediated isothermal amplification.

label.value: blood meal assay

definition.value: An assay that analyzes the specimen taken from blood meal fed organism, such as insect.

label.value: blood meal by counter current immunoelectrophoresis assay

definition.value: A blood meal assay that uses a counter current immunoelectrophoresis technique.

label.value: DNA based blood meal finger printing assay

definition.value: A DNA fingerprinting assay that uses DNA extracted from blood meal fed organism, such as insect.

label.value: organism detection by size assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that is based on the size of organism.

label.value: organism detection by cross mating assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that is based on genetic crossings between specimens collected in the field to determine whether fertile progeny is produced.

label.value: organism detection by cytological chromosome examination assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that is based on analysis of polytene chromosomes through cytological examination of the banding pattern of the species.
